Whereas it is estimated that 40,000,000 individuals in the United States, 13 percent of the
			 population of the United States, are 65 years of age or
			 older;

Whereas by 2060, the population of individuals in the United States who are age 65 or older is
			 projected to increase from 1 out of 7 individuals to 1 out of 5
			 individuals;

Whereas 1 out of 5 individuals in the United States who are older than 65 years of age need
			 assistance from a
			 caregiver to complete activities of daily living;
